### Contingency Planning (CP) — Administrative Procedures

---

**CP-2: Contingency Plan**

**Implementation Status:** Partially Implemented — Technical recovery procedures documented; clinical downtime procedures in development

**Implementation Description:**

MyClinic maintains a Contingency Plan for the OpenMRS system. The plan has two components that must both be functional for the contingency program to be complete:

*Technical recovery procedures (implemented):*
The technical recovery section of the contingency plan documents: the RTO target (4 hours), the RPO target (24 hours), the step-by-step procedure for restoring OpenMRS from the most recent S3 backup to a new RDS instance, the procedure for restoring the EC2 application server from a current AMI, the procedure for updating DNS configuration if the EC2 IP address changes during recovery, and verification steps to confirm the restored system is functional before clinical use resumes.

The technical recovery procedures are written at the task level — specific enough for the IT Administrator to execute them under the stress of a real incident without needing to make judgment calls about the sequence of steps.

*Clinical downtime procedures (partially implemented — POA&M item):*
Clinical downtime procedures documenting how clinical staff operate during OpenMRS unavailability are in development. This is the gap identified as V-015 in the vulnerability inventory and referenced throughout the Categorize step analysis. The absence of functional, tested clinical downtime procedures was a factor in the High availability categorization.

Current status: a draft downtime procedure has been produced that covers patient registration in paper mode and basic encounter documentation. The draft has not been reviewed by clinical staff, has not been tested in a downtime exercise, and does not cover medication management, laboratory result handling, or care plan management in downtime mode. The ISSO has committed to completing, reviewing, and testing clinical downtime procedures before the authorization package is finalized.

**POA&M Reference:** CP-2 clinical downtime procedures — target completion date [specified in POA&M]; owner: Health IT Manager and ISSO jointly.

**Assessment Evidence:** Contingency plan document (both sections); clinical downtime procedures (draft — assessor should note POA&M status); technical recovery procedures.

---

**CP-3: Contingency Training**

**Implementation Status:** Partially Implemented

**Implementation Description:**

IT staff contingency training covering the technical recovery procedures is conducted annually. Training includes a walkthrough of the recovery procedure documentation and a discussion of the most recent backup restoration test results.

Clinical staff contingency training on downtime procedures is planned but cannot be conducted until the clinical downtime procedures are complete and reviewed. This training is a POA&M item dependent on CP-2 clinical downtime procedure completion.

**Assessment Evidence:** IT staff training records; clinical staff training plan (pending CP-2 completion).

---

**CP-4: Contingency Plan Testing**

**Implementation Status:** Partially Implemented

**Implementation Description:**

*Quarterly backup restoration test (implemented):*
The ISSO and IT Administrator conduct a restoration test each quarter. The test procedure: restore the most recent weekly S3 backup to a test RDS instance in the AWS account; verify that the test instance is accessible; spot-check a defined set of data fields against the expected values from the backup date; document the restoration time from initiation to verified completion; compare actual restoration time against the 4-hour RTO target; document any deviation and remediation action.

Test results are documented in a restoration test log maintained by the ISSO. Any test that reveals a restoration failure or RTO miss triggers an immediate investigation and remediation before the next quarterly test.

*Annual tabletop exercise (implemented):*
The annual tabletop exercise (documented under IR-3) includes contingency scenarios in rotation. A dedicated contingency tabletop exercise simulating extended system unavailability is scheduled annually.

*Full alternate processing site test (planned — POA&M item):*
A full test of restoration to an alternate AWS region — the CP-4(2) enhancement requirement — has not yet been conducted. This is a POA&M item dependent on establishing the alternate region infrastructure documented in the CP-7 planning.

**Assessment Evidence:** Restoration test log showing quarterly results; most recent restoration test report with actual restoration time; tabletop exercise records.

